cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper is primarily focused on Chinese word segmentation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the scope of cs.CL.
2. cs.LG (Learning) - The proposed model uses LSTM and self-attention structures, which are commonly used in deep learning and machine learning, and hence, this paper could also be categorized under cs.LG.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of deep learning techniques and neural networks in this paper makes it relevant to the field of AI.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed model is a neural network-based approach, and hence, this paper could also be categorized under cs.NE.
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - Chinese word segmentation is an important task in information retrieval, and hence, this paper could also be categorized under cs.IR.
